\
Response:\
P4 (Programming Protocol-Independent Packet Processors) is a domain-specific programming language designed for defining how network devices (such as switches, routers, and firewalls) process packets. Unlike traditional fixed-function network devices that have predefined behaviors, P4 allows network operators to program the data plane, enabling custom packet processing logic.\
